A warm welcome to the tiniest penguin on Earth.

The world's smallest penguin species has welcomed a delightful new arrival: Henry, a fairy penguin chick who hatched at SEA LIFE Weymouth in Dorset, UK.

Also known as little blue penguins for their striking blue-grey feathers that shimmer in the water, fairy penguins are the smallest of all penguin kinds. Adults typically stand just 30–40 cm tall—roughly the height of a standard loaf of bread—compared to the much taller emperor penguins.

Franklin’s resurgence started when a combat-styled meme of the classic 90s turtle suddenly went viral on X. The internet ran with it—remixing it, evolving it, and turning Franklin into a symbol of humor, rebellion, and nostalgia. What began as a single image quickly became a full-blown movement, with thousands of users creating their own versions and pushing Franklin back into the spotlight. Now the community has brought Franklin into Web3, transforming an iconic childhood character into a modern memecoin on Solana—driven by creativity, culture, and the chaotic fun of the internet.
